# Trivy allowlist.
#
# Each line is either a Trivy finding ID (whatever Trivy emits — CVE-...,
# GHSA-..., AVD-..., DS-..., KSV001 without hyphen, lowercase secret-rule
# IDs like `aws-access-token`, etc.) or a `#`-prefixed comment. Per
# ADR-0027 §Negative and docs/ops/dep-management.md §Allowlist, each
# entry must satisfy three machine-enforced rules (gated in CI by
# scripts/check-allowlist-schema.sh):
#
#   1. A `# owner: @<github-handle>` comment in the contiguous comment
#      block immediately preceding the entry. <github-handle> must be a
#      valid GitHub handle (1-39 alnum chars + non-leading/trailing/
#      consecutive hyphens) — `@-`, `@:`, etc. are rejected.
#   2. A `# reason: <free text>` comment in the same block.
#   3. An `exp:YYYY-MM-DD` suffix on the entry line itself, within
#      [today, today+90d].
#
# Example:
#
#   # owner: @vlzware
#   # reason: CVE on libfoo (image base layer) — exploit requires
#   #         inbound TCP on 9000; our image binds only 8080.
#   CVE-2026-12345 exp:2026-08-16
#
# Trivy itself reads only the entry IDs; the comment block is the review
# contract enforced by the schema check, not by Trivy.
#
# (no active entries)
